'''处女'''（{{lang-en|virginity}}）指的是女性没有性行为经验的一种状态<ref name="Virginity">{{cite dictionary|title=Virginity|dictionary=[[Merriam-Webster|Merriam-Webster]]|access-date=December 21, 2013|url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/virginity|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111233319/https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/virginity|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Virginity2">{{cite web|title=Virginity|publisher=[[TheFreeDictionary.com|TheFreeDictionary.com]]|access-date=December 21, 2013|url=http://www.thefreedictionary.com/Virgin|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213145246/https://www.thefreedictionary.com/virgin|dead-url=no}}</ref>。广义上是指无论男女都没有发生过性行为的人——涵盖了[[處男|處男]]在内。

在人類文化與宗教信仰传统上對此賦予特殊的價值觀與重要意義，特別是片面要求女性[[守贞|守贞]]的社会中，未婚女性的“處女”，代表著個人的純淨、[[名譽|榮譽]]與品格價值。狹義傳統上處女鑒定的標誌為[[處女膜|處女膜]]，但是[[现代医学|现代医学]]技术可以修補，同时，處女膜也未必只因性交而損傷，少部分人天生就沒落紅，目前沒有絕對的鑑別方法。

== 处女 ==
對大多數來說，處女是指沒有發生過[[陰道性交|陰道性交]]的女子<ref name="Carpenter"/><ref name="consent">{{cite news| first = Laura M.| last = Carpenter| title = The Ambiguity of "Having Sex": The Subjective Experience of Virginity Loss in the United States - Statistical Data Included| url = http://www.popline.org/node/252980| publisher = [[The_Journal_of_Sex_Research|The Journal of Sex Research]]| location = United States| year = 2001| accessdate = June 5, 2012| archive-date = 2019-06-17| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190617082854/https://www.popline.org/node/252980| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="Intimate">{{Cite book|author=Bryan Strong, Christine DeVault, Theodore F. Cohen|title=The Marriage and Family Experience: Intimate Relationship in a Changing Society| publisher = [[Cengage_Learning|Cengage Learning]]|year = 2010|accessdate=October 8, 2011 |page = 186| isbn = 0-534-62425-1|url=http://books.google.com/?id=qjvoSOMB5JMC&pg=PA186|quote=Most people agree that we maintain virginity as long as we refrain from sexual (vaginal) intercourse. But occasionally we hear people speak of 'technical virginity' [...] Data indicate that 'a very significant proportion of teens ha[ve] had experience with oral sex, even if they haven't had sexual intercourse, and may think of themselves as virgins' [...] Other research, especially research looking into virginity loss, reports that 35% of virgins, defined as people who have never engaged in vaginal intercourse, have nonetheless engaged in one or more other forms of heterosexual sexual activity (e.g., oral sex, anal sex, or mutual masturbation).}}</ref><ref name="Blank">{{Cite book|title=Virgin: The Untouched History| publisher = [[Bloomsbury_Publishing|Bloomsbury Publishing]] USA|year = 2008|accessdate=October 8, 2011 |pages = 304 pages| isbn = 1-59691-011-9|url=http://books.google.com/?id=V6IPvgFKGFUC&pg=PA253&dq=virginity+loss+among+lesbians#v=onepage&q=virginity%20loss%20among%20lesbians&f=false|author=Hanne Blank}}</ref> ，即指[[男性|男性]][[陰莖|陰莖]]插入女性[[陰道|陰道]]的性交，和因[[性交|性交]]而令[[處女膜|處女膜]]破損的[[性交|性交]]<ref name="Carpenter"/><ref name="Intimate"/><ref name="Friedman">{{Cite news|last=Friedman |first=Mindy |title=Sex on Tuesday: Virginity: A Fluid Issue |work=The Daily Californian |date=September 20, 2005 |url=http://www.dailycal.org/article/19565/sex_on_tuesday_virginity_a_fluid_issue |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090506021934/http://www.dailycal.org/article/19565/sex_on_tuesday_virginity_a_fluid_issue |archivedate=2009-05-06 |accessdate=October 6, 2011 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="McAnulty">{{Cite book|author= Richard D. McAnulty, M. Michele Burnette |title=Making Healthy Decisions| publisher = [[Allyn_&_Bacon|Allyn & Bacon]]|year = 2000 |page = 229 | isbn = 0-205-19519-9}}</ref>。但是有些天生處女膜偏厚的女性，[[初夜|初夜]]時處女膜不一定會破裂，破裂也不一定在初夜時。

而精確上，處女是指沒有發生任何與他人有互動的[[人類性行為|性行為]]的女子，包括：[[陰道性交|陰道性交]]、[[肛交|肛交]]、[[口交|口交]]、[[乳交|乳交]]、彼此間的[[自慰|自慰]]、[[愛撫|愛撫]]或視訊性交等。<ref name="Carpenter"/><ref name="Blank"/><ref name="Virgin">{{cite book|first=Michael|last=Joseph Gross|title = Like a Virgin|id = 0001-8996|publisher=''[[The_Advocate|The Advocate]]'', Here Publishing|year=2003|page=45|accessdate=2011-03-13|url=http://books.google.com/?id=eWQEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA44&dq=Gay+men+who+prefer+anal+sex#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>

所謂的[[技術性處女|技術性處女]]，即在沒有損傷處女膜的狀況下與他人進行各種廣義的性交行為卻自稱處女者。或者處女膜因與他人性交而受損，卻藉由人工方式修補處女膜來詐稱處女者，但如同[[技術性處男|技術性處男]]，二詞定義時常淪落於陰莖插入本位。

== 處男 ==
{{Details|處男}}
[[處男|處男]]則是對應於處女，用於男性的名詞。英語為「cherry boy」，日語漢字寫作「童貞」。不過由於男性難以區分處男與否，故往往強調處女而不著重處男這一觀念。由於處男沒法像處女一樣經由處女膜的破損流血來判斷，故古代封建觀念裡總是不太譴責男性的風流花心，而當類似的行為發生在女性身上便引發極端強烈的抨擊，而總是單方要求女性將性行為與婚姻合一。

== 社会文化中的“处女” ==

=== 处女情结和检验贞操 ===
如同[[贞操|贞操]]觀念，處子的觀念在傳統上包括在婚姻之前的節欲（避免[[婚前性行為|婚前性行為]]）以及結婚後只以婚配對象為性伴侶。贞操通常涉及[[性倫理|伦理道德]]或宗教问题，可以带来社会地位方面和[[人际关系|人际关系]]的影响。<ref name="Carpenter">See here [http://books.google.com/books?id=6qNCeI2AcY4C&pg=PT11&lpg=PT11] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=6qNCeI2AcY4C&pg=PT11&lpg=PT11 |date=20210219092951 }} and [http://books.google.com/books?id=pXXZn_qSoDoC&pg=PA48 pages 47-49] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=pXXZn_qSoDoC&pg=PA48 |date=20150318170410 }} for views on what constitutes virginity loss and therefore sexual intercourse or other sexual activity; source discusses how gay and lesbian individuals define virginity loss, and how the majority of researchers and heterosexuals define virginity loss/"technical virginity" by whether or not a person has engaged in penile-vaginal sex. {{Cite book|author=Laura M. Carpenter|title=Virginity Lost: An Intimate Portrait of First Sexual Experiences|publisher=[[New_York_University|NYU Press]]|year=2005|accessdate=October 9, 2011|pages=295 pages|isbn=0-8147-1652-0|url=http://books.google.com/?id=pXXZn_qSoDoC|quote=}}</ref><ref name="Bennett">{{Cite book|author=Linda Rae Bennett|title=Women, Islam and modernity: single women, sexuality and reproductive health in contemporary Indonesia|publisher=Psychology Press|year = 2005 |accessdate=October 9, 2011|pages=183 pages |isbn=0-415-32929-9|url=http://books.google.com/?id=JaA1kxjMebEC&pg=PA19&dq=male+virginity#v=onepage&q=male%20virginity&f=false}}</ref>虽然贞操有社会影响，并在过去曾在一些社会中有相关法律，但当今大多数社会中没有法律涉及这个问题。

一些社會著重女性在出嫁前一定不發生[[婚前性行為|婚前性行為]]，守贞成为判断女性价值的标准。故此，各地都存在不尽相同的检验女性贞操的方法。《[[圣经|圣经]]》提及“叫妇人蓬头散发，站在耶和华面前”以“素餐”起誓，并喝下“致诅咒的苦水”。《[[旧约|旧约]]·民数记》第五章说“她若受污，喝了这苦水，肚腹要发胀，大腿要消瘦。”[[匈牙利|匈牙利]]的[[齐格纳人|齐格纳人]]，要求新娘赤脚踏上[[菩提树|菩提树]]制作的小圆板，新娘若失贞，则会有灾难。另一种方式是以[[黄杨树|黄杨树]]枝穿三只剥皮后的[[喜鹊|喜鹊]]头，放在新娘枕下。新娘若失贞会在梦话中坦白，守贞的新娘则会安睡。中国传统文学和民间傳說中，亦有各种判斷處女的方法。如[[守宮砂|守宮砂]]、滴血、验枕骨、看眉毛和腿型等，不一而足<ref>{{cite book |last= |first= |date= |author=冯国超 |title=中国古代性学报告（增补版） |chapter=第一章 性与中国古代的婚姻家庭 二、贞操观、节妇及非婚性行为 1.新婚女子必须是处女 |url=http://yuedu.163.com/source/713f58c9ed554f8fa56e57dda6af049d_4 |dead-url=yes |location= |publisher=华夏出版社 |isbn= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115204212/http://yuedu.163.com/source/713f58c9ed554f8fa56e57dda6af049d_4 |archive-date=2017-11-15 |accessdate=2017-12-01 |language=Zh-hans }}</ref>。守宮砂之说则常見於[[武俠小說|武俠小說]]，如《[[神雕俠侶|神雕俠侶]]》的[[小龍女|小龍女]]因失身而造成[[守宮砂|守宮砂]]消失。

=== 处女的首次性交 ===
處男或處女的首次性交皆稱[[初夜|初夜]]，相对于男性，在要求女性守贞社会中，女性的初夜在社会文化中更为关注。占有女性初夜，在某些時期的部分人類社會，形成所謂的[[初夜權|初夜權]]的概念。

占有女性初夜的另一种动机，是认为与处女性交可以治愈疾病。这类民间说法，可追溯至16世纪的[[欧洲|欧洲]]。在当代[[非洲|非洲]]，则盛兴[[处女艾滋清除说|处女艾滋清除说]]，增加女性被[[强奸|强奸]]的风险。

=== 中國大陸 ===
近代以来，[[中华人民共和国性文化|中国社会风气对性已较为开放]]，但片面要求女性婚前守贞的“处女情结”仍普遍存在。[[贞操嫁妆论|贞操嫁妆论]]，时有讨论。接受高等教育的年轻人仍会受到这一思想禁锢（如[[包丽自杀事件|包丽自杀事件]]）。更有女性为夫寻找处女强奸进而杀人的极端案件（如[[胡伊萱案|胡伊萱案]]）。占有女性初夜，亦成为男性追逐的目标，官员和权贵阶层“[[买处|买处]]”成风。各色人等通常在中、小学生中寻找“目标”，以致强奸案件频发。官员“买处”的动机一是“处女情结”下的占有处女<ref name="a1"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.huaxia.com/gd/cf/2006/00461080.html |title=17名幼女被买处的幕后故事 |accessdate=2017-12-01 |author=记者：贾云勇 |date=2006-05-25 |work= |publisher=华夏经纬网，来源：南方新闻网 |language=Zh-hans |archive-date=2017-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201143302/http://www.huaxia.com/gd/cf/2006/00461080.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，二是改善[[运气|运气]]，提升官运，与传统[[冲喜|冲喜]]之说相关<ref name="a1">{{Cite web |url=http://news.sina.com.cn/zl/zatan/2015-01-14/14273023.shtml |title=拿什么来终结向学生“买处”？ |accessdate=2017-12-01 |author=王传涛 |date=2015-01-14 |work= |publisher=新浪网 |language=Zh-hans |archive-date=2019-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190613010912/http://news.sina.com.cn/zl/zatan/2015-01-14/14273023.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
